<h5>Enrollment</h5>
<p>Some initial information is required to enroll. Our enrollments are risk-free—nothing will be charged until the Blood cells received, processed, and cryo-preserved. If the person later decides not to store, the he should inform it to Medicare Tech immediately to avoid any fees.</p>
<p>At the place of enrollment, you will find a client agreement, which needs to be completed and send as soon as possible. In addition, you will find forms for the client to fill out. These forms go over the personal health history  and collection point data means home address and provide other necessary medical details.</p>
<p>The parents should also notify their doctor of their plans if to store their children’s( Children age above 12 and below 18) blood cells. </p>
<h5>Collection</h5>
<p>Before taking samples initial blood samples are collected to be tested for certain infectious diseases (Hepatitis, Hemophilia, HIV and Cancer) as mandated in regulations. If a person willing to use mobile service he or she can Request of the mobile service and acquire the facility. It conducts two days (Tuesday and Friday) per week. The Transportation charges may differ according to the distance. But constant payment acquire for the investigation. Total Payment varies with the transportation cost. After Initial test approved then only a person can go for giving sample</p>
<p> After the initial test approved and lab report delivered, the blood sample is then collected manually by visitng the Laboratory. There is absolutely no pain or risk to the elder person or child during the collection process because the blood is taken from the hand after it has been clamped and cut. </p>
       <h5>Transportation</h5>
       <p>Within two hours of delivery, a call should be made to Medi Tech to arrange for the laboratory Report. This call should be made at (6 AM to 10 PM) time, 24 hours a day. The medical courier will often provide a four-hour window for his or her arrival. The medical courier will then see to the proper transportation of the Blood sample (initial Test) to the laboratory.</p>
       <h5>Testing and Processing</h5>
       <p>After donating the Blood cells, usually within 36 to 48 hours of collection, the blood cells are tested, processed, and cryogenically stored.
• Each specimen is tested for microbiological contamination.
• The cryo cells is then processed to maximize the recovery of stem cells by Medi Tech’s specialized laboratory technologists.
Person has to pay an annual fee for acquiring storage facility. By the way it can be paid in three installments. 
</p>
<h5>Preservation</h5>
<p>All samples are overwrapped for extra protection against cross-contamination during storage. All specimens are stored in the vapor phase of liquid nitrogen for cryogenic preservation, at temperatures below −170 degrees Celsius, or approximately −274 degrees Fahrenheit.</p>
<p>We are the only private cord blood bank available in our area that takes these measures during the banking process because we want to preserve additional samples for the possible future benefit of our clients including any future developments in medical science. Here is how a family may one day benefit from these additional samples:</p>
<p>•  New ways of discovering agents of disease could prevent infectious stem cells from being transplanted to another family member.
• Genetic testing could be needed for the mother or the child.
• If any relation or a family member met with an accident, leukemia, Haemophilia like blood related disease this may very much helpful.
• Re-tests may be required because of misidentification caused by hospital errors or questionable lab results.
</p>
<p> Owner of the sample can request for sample incineration (which means discarding). He or she can check the status of the sample anytime etc.

</p>
